<li id="cite_note-Lincoln2003-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Lincoln2003_18-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLincoln_G.2C_Andersson_H.2C_Loudon_A2003">Lincoln G, Andersson H, Loudon A (2003). "Clock genes in calendar cells as the basis of annual timekeeping in mammals — a unifying hypothesis". <i>J Endocrinol</i> <b>179</b> (1): 1 – 13. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1677%2Fjoe.0.1790001" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1677%2Fjoe.0.1790001" rel="nofollow">10.1677/joe.0.1790001</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14529560" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14529560">PMID 14529560</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Clock+genes+in+calendar+cells+as+the+basis+of+annual+timekeeping+in+mammals+%E2%80%94+a+unifying+hypothesis&amp;rft.jtitle=J+Endocrinol&amp;rft.aulast=Lincoln+G%2C+Andersson+H%2C+Loudon+A&amp;rft.au=Lincoln+G%2C+Andersson+H%2C+Loudon+A&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.volume=179&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=1+%E2%80%93+13&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1677%2Fjoe.0.1790001&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/14529560&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Melatonin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Arendt2005-19">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Arendt2005_19-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Arendt2005_19-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFArendt_J.2C_Skene_DJ2005">Arendt J, Skene DJ (2005). "Melatonin as a chronobiotic". <i>Sleep Med Rev</i> <b>9</b> (1): 25–39. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.smrv.2004.05.002" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.smrv.2004.05.002" rel="nofollow">10.1016/j.smrv.2004.05.002</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15649736" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15649736">PMID 15649736</a>.  "Exogenous melatonin has acute sleepiness-inducing and temperature-lowering effects during 'biological daytime', and when suitably timed (it is most effective around dusk and dawn) it will shift the phase of the human circadian clock (sleep, endogenous melatonin, core body temperature, cortisol) to earlier (advance phase shift) or later (delay phase shift) times.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Melatonin+as+a+chronobiotic&amp;rft.jtitle=Sleep+Med+Rev&amp;rft.aulast=Arendt+J%2C+Skene+DJ&amp;rft.au=Arendt+J%2C+Skene+DJ&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=9&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=25%E2%80%9339&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1016%2Fj.smrv.2004.05.002&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/15649736&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Melatonin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Chaturvedi-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Chaturvedi_20-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCM_Chaturvedi1984">CM Chaturvedi (1984). "<a href="http://www.publish.csiro.au/paper/ZO9840803.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.publish.csiro.au/paper/ZO9840803.htm" rel="nofollow">Effect of Melatonin on the Adrenl and Gonad of the Common Mynah Acridtheres tristis</a>". <i>Australian Journal of Zoology</i> <b>32</b> (6): 803 – 809. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1071%2FZO9840803" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1071%2FZO9840803" rel="nofollow">10.1071/ZO9840803</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.publish.csiro.au/paper/ZO9840803.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.publish.csiro.au/paper/ZO9840803.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.publish.csiro.au/paper/ZO9840803.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Effect+of+Melatonin+on+the+Adrenl+and+Gonad+of+the+Common+Mynah+Acridtheres+tristis&amp;rft.jtitle=Australian+Journal+of+Zoology&amp;rft.aulast=CM+Chaturvedi&amp;rft.au=CM+Chaturvedi&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.volume=32&amp;rft.issue=6&amp;rft.pages=803+%E2%80%93+809&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1071%2FZO9840803&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.publish.csiro.au%2Fpaper%2FZO9840803.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Melatonin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
